# AgentFlow V3 — Cursor Development Prompt

## Project Context

AgentFlow V3 is an AI agent superapp on Arc Network (Circle's L1 blockchain).
It is NOT a research tool anymore. V3 is a full DeFi execution platform where
autonomous AI agents execute real onchain transactions via Circle Developer
Controlled Wallets (DCW), powered by Hermes 4 LLM via Nous Portal API.

## Repository Structure

```
C:\Users\ASUS\agent-economy\          ← agentflow-backend (root)
C:\Users\ASUS\agent-economy\agentflow-frontend\  ← Next.js frontend (subfolder only; see agentflow-frontend-layout.mdc)
```

**Frontend placement:** All Next.js / UI files go under `agentflow-frontend/` — never a second app at repo root. See **`.cursor/rules/agentflow-frontend-layout.mdc`** (always on).

## Tech Stack

### Backend (agent-economy root)
- Node.js + TypeScript + Express
- Supabase (Postgres) — persistent storage
- Redis (ioredis) — rate limiting + session cache
- Circle Developer Controlled Wallets SDK
- @circlefin/x402-batching — micropayments
- viem — Arc RPC calls
- Hermes 4 via Nous Portal API (OpenAI-compatible)
- Firecrawl (self-hosted on Hetzner VPS)
- Resend — email inbound/outbound
- node-cron — scheduled agents
- Circle Bridge Kit — CCTP V2 Fast Transfer

### Frontend (agentflow-frontend/)
- Next.js 14 + TypeScript
- RainbowKit + wagmi
- Tailwind CSS
- Supabase client

