# PHASE 8 — Chrome Extension

**Goal:** Premium research companion. URL-only, user-initiated.
Open source from day one.

## Permissions (Minimal — Chrome Web Store Approved)

```json
{
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "permissions": ["activeTab", "storage"],
  "host_permissions": []
}
```

NO content scripts reading page DOM.
NO background tab reading.
ONLY reads current tab URL on explicit user click.

## Flow

```
User opens extension popup
Extension loads wallet summary from AgentFlow API (JWT auth)
User types question
User clicks Analyze
Extension sends: { url: currentTab.url, question, walletAddress, jwt }
Backend fetches page content via Firecrawl (not extension)
Hermes 70B analyzes: fetched content + wallet context + question
Streams response back to extension popup via SSE
Extension shows what was sent (transparency):
  ✓ Current page URL
  ✓ Your question
  ✓ Wallet address (read only)
  ✗ Page content — fetched by server, not sent by extension
  ✗ Private keys — never
  ✗ Other tabs — never
```

## Files

```
agentflow-extension/
├── manifest.json
├── background.ts       ← service worker, auth + API calls
├── popup/
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── App.tsx
│   └── components/
│       ├── WalletSummary.tsx
│       ├── QueryInput.tsx
│       ├── MacroResult.tsx
│       └── UsageIndicator.tsx  ← shows 10/day remaining
└── lib/
    ├── api.ts          ← sends {url, question, walletAddress, jwt}
    └── auth.ts         ← verifies premium JWT
```

## Chrome Web Store Submission

- Category: Productivity (NOT Finance — avoids extra scrutiny)
- Privacy policy required at agentflow.one/privacy
- Statement: "This extension never accesses private keys, seed phrases, or wallet credentials"
- Beta: distribute as unpacked .zip to 20 testers first
- Submit to Chrome Web Store minimum 3 weeks before public launch

