# Critical Rules — Never Break These

1. **Wallet data in Supabase only** — never in files, never in runtime .env
2. **getOrCreateWallet pattern** — always check DB before creating
3. **Withdrawals never rate limited** — emergency-withdraw bypasses everything
4. **Free tx cap is $100 USDC** — enforce before every DCW execution
5. **Use arc-config.ts** — never hardcode chain IDs or contract addresses
6. **Two Supabase clients** — adminDb (backend) and clientDb (frontend)
7. **Stream all LLM responses** — never block, always stream via SSE
8. **Hermes 70B for fast** — extension + quick queries
9. **Hermes 405B for deep** — research reports + portfolio analysis
10. **GPT-4o for vision** — invoice image parsing only
11. **ERC-8004 already deployed** — do NOT redeploy those contracts
12. **Arc CCTP domain is 7** — always use Bridge Kit, never raw CCTP
13. **Self-hosted Firecrawl** — on Hetzner VPS, not cloud API
14. **ioredis with connection pooling** — never single Redis client
15. **V2 agents unchanged** — research/analyst/writer carry over as-is

